<span class="displaytext"><b>chapel hill, north carolina</b> – today, (candidate full) for president communications director chris kofinis released the following statement on the definition of mudslinging: <p>"mudslinging |må­d'slä­ng'ing| (also <b>mud-slinging</b>)noun <i>informal</i><br/> the use of insults and accusations, esp. unjust ones, with the aim of damaging the reputation of an opponent. as in: (candidate full) said about (candidate full), 'now voters will judge whether living in a foreign country at the age of 10 prepares one to face the big, complex international challenges the next president will face.' </p><p>"now we know what senator (candidate last) meant when she talked about 'throwing mud' in the last debate. like so many other things, when it comes to mud, (candidate full) says one thing and throws another."</p></span>



